name: Sen. Dan Sullivan
tweet_text: So today we organized this summit with four goals in mind: (1)To bring federal, state and local officials together to coordinate efforts. (2) To paint a picture for the federal officials here about the unique challenges that we face here in Alaska in countering drug trafficking.

tweet_text: The vast majority of this is fueled by the drug epidemic. But here is the good news. We are Alaskans. We are tough, we are resilient and we innovative. There is no doubt in my mind that we can conquer this.

name: Sen. Dan Sullivan
tweet_text: Its critical to remember that behind these statistics and numbers is a personal story of a fellow Alaskan and their family of heartbreak, tragedy, sorrow and anger. #ConfrontingAKCrimeWave

name: Sen. Dan Sullivan
tweet_text: In the last 5 years the murder rate in Alaska is up 79%. Rape is up 16%. Assault is up 36%. Robbery is up 52%. Vehicle theft is up 150%. Burglary is up 42%. #ConfrontingAKCrimeWave

tweet_text: Nearly every day I hear from Alaskans about cars stolen and houses broken into. Shootings on our streets. Just days ago the Alaska Dept. of Safety put out their annual crime report. The numbers are staggering. #ConfrontingAKCrimeWave

name: Sen. Dan Sullivan
tweet_text: Yesterday, the Minority Leader had a choice. Sadly, he decided to turn a manufactured crisis into a government shutdown. https://t.co/2BDeNxYmwm

name: Sen. Dan Sullivan
tweet_text: As work continues, I am hopeful that we can find a solution to reopen the government.  The American people, particularly our veterans & troops, deserve better. My office stands ready to assist Alaskans, including those negatively impacted by this unnecessary government shutdown.

name: Sen. Dan Sullivan
tweet_text: I simply fail to understand the logic behind the Minority Leader‚Äôs decision to shut down the govt. Passage of the CR tonight would have continued the essential functions of govt, provided funding for CHIP & given Congress an opportunity to address a long term spending measure.

name: Sen. Dan Sullivan
tweet_text: The bipartisan bill we considered tonight, which funded the government until February 16th, was voted down not for the items it contained, but for what was not included ‚Äì a long term agreement on immigration for which we still have weeks to resolve.

name: Sen. Dan Sullivan
tweet_text: Tonight, we saw a manufactured crisis officially turn into a government shutdown ‚Äì something that was absolutely preventable.

name: Sen. Dan Sullivan
tweet_text: The bill before us prevents a government shutdown, funds CHIP for six years and delays a number of harmful Obamacare taxes. While a resolution on immigration reform is important, funding the government must take priority.

name: Sen. Dan Sullivan
tweet_text: While I believe a resolution on immigration reform ‚Äì one that includes an increase in border security ‚Äì should occur, keeping the government open and operational must take priority.

name: Sen. Dan Sullivan
tweet_text: The short-term funding measure currently before us, which I support, contains numerous provisions that enjoy nearly universal backing in Alaska and Congress ‚Äì including a six year extension of CHIP and delays to Obamacare‚Äôs Cadillac and Medical Device taxes.

name: Sen. Dan Sullivan
tweet_text: Yet tonight, in the face of a government shutdown, the Senate Minority Leader is now emphasizing an issue he has rarely focused on ‚Äì rebuilding our military ‚Äì while failing to mention his primary reason for shutting down the govt ‚Äì a lack of an agreement on immigration reform.

name: Sen. Dan Sullivan
tweet_text: For months, Congress has worked to debate and negotiate a long term spending measure ‚Äì one that appropriately supports our men and women in uniform, establishes policies that grow our economy, and tackles a series of leading national priorities.

name: Sen. Dan Sullivan
tweet_text: The only thing worse than another Continuing Resolution ‚Äì particularly for our military and veterans ‚Äì is a government shutdown.
